    "shortDesc": "Cough, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Cough, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Cough, unspecified means a patient has a cough, but the doctor hasn't determined the specific cause or type yet. The cough could be dry, wet, persistent, or occasional—and it might be from a cold, allergies, asthma, acid reflux, or many other reasons. This code is used temporarily when the underlying reason for the cough is still being investigated or remains unknown.",
