    "plainEnglish": "This code describes unusual blood sugar levels that don't fit neatly into other glucose categories—meaning your blood sugar is abnormal in some way, but it's not a straightforward case of diabetes or hypoglycemia. It could mean your glucose is slightly elevated, fluctuating oddly, or showing patterns that your doctor wants to investigate further. You might not have any symptoms, as this is typically found during blood work or routine screening.",
