    "longDesc": "Other specified abnormal findings of blood chemistry",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes unexpected or unusual results in a blood test that don't fit into other specific categories—think of it as a catch-all for blood chemistry findings that are abnormal but don't have their own dedicated code. Your blood was tested and something showed up that's different from normal, such as an electrolyte imbalance, enzyme level, or other chemical component, but the specific cause or nature of the abnormality needs further investigation or doesn't match a more precise diagnosis code.",
